'''National Public Radio''', or '''NPR''', is a commercial-free radio venture in the United States which reaches an audience of 26 million people daily.

NPR produced and broadcast [[1981]] [[Star Wars (radio)|''Star Wars'']] and [[1983]] [[The Empire Strikes Back (radio)|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] radio drama adaptations. The third series in the trilogy, [[Return of the Jedi (radio)|''Return of the Jedi'']] ([[1996]]), was produced by [[HighBridge Audio]], an affiliate of Minnesota Public Radio, and broadcast on NPR.<ref name="Encyclopedia">{{BookCite|author=Christopher H. Sterling |title=Encyclopedia of Radio |number=vol. 3 |publisher=Routledge |date=2004 |isbn=9781135456498 |link=https://books.google.com/books?id=-UeveLMilioC&dq=Frank%20Mankiewicz%20star%20wars&pg=PA2206 }}</ref>

Several ''Star Wars''&ndash;themed programs were aired in [[2005]] during the run-up to the release of [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']], including an interview with composer [[John Williams]], reviews of the movie, and more.

